 New Item: 
"​Creativity and Healing in the Arts" 
A presentation by Tad Dunne at Common Dialog Day, October 2018


You must be still learning.
After all, here  you are, still on the journey.

Learning may seem like hiking: Just start hiking and you get the hang of it. But most of what you learn will be from wandering into swamps and getting lost. This is why we have schools. Whether you're hiking or learning, you can learn from others how to avoid swamps and keep your bearings in the first place.

So to get the maximum out of learning anything, it will help first to learn what others have learned about learning. This is what this site is all about.

We have four topics: Just click on any of these items below or in the menu at the top:

Intelligence,  Strategies,  Communicating,  Faith.
